<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module ships ONE deliberate counter-example whose data race IS the lesson, so a test can
    prove the lost update the prose describes rather than merely assert it. The Multithreaded-
    correctness detectors are left fully ENABLED for the rest of the module (the atomic, synchronized,
    final-publication, holder, and coordinator types all stay clean); only the named racy counter
    carries a finding, suppressed narrowly, with a reason, and pointed at the test that demonstrates
    why it matters. Fixing the class — which AtomicCounter and SynchronizedCounter already do — is the
    real advice; the suppression exists only so the teaching counter-example can ship green.
  -->

  <!--
    RacyCounter.increment() runs count++ on a volatile field, a read-modify-write that is not atomic,
    so concurrent callers can lose increments — the hook's bug. At this module's threshold the pinned
    SpotBugs (4.9.x) raises TWO Multithreaded-correctness findings on the increment() body, both
    verified against the build:
      - VO_VOLATILE_INCREMENT ("Increment of volatile field ... is not atomic"), the named pattern the
        chapter prose calls out for volatile++; and
      - AT_NONATOMIC_OPERATIONS_ON_SHARED_VARIABLE ("Operation on shared variable is not atomic"), the
        broader atomicity-violation pattern that also fires once the field is read by count().
    SpotBugs surfaces one at a time by priority, so both are matched here; either alone leaves the
    other to fail the build (verified by suppressing each in turn). The suppressions are load-bearing,
    not decorative. Proven by ThreadSafetyContractTest#racyCounterCanLoseUpdatesUnderContention. The
    fix is an atomic (AtomicCounter) or a lock (SynchronizedCounter), never this suppression.
  -->
  <Match>
    <Class name="org.acme.concurrency.RacyCounter"/>
    <Bug pattern="VO_VOLATILE_INCREMENT,AT_NONATOMIC_OPERATIONS_ON_SHARED_VARIABLE"/>
  </Match>
</FindBugsFilter>
